_json.gridTitle: A 1930s Texas Cottage Gets Major Curb Appeal
_json.description: When Royce first bought his home, he fell in love with its architectural elements, but the red window covers, brown grass, and the barely standing wooden fence in the backyard were more than an eyesore. He decided to preserve the structure of the home including most of the wood siding and give it a modern touch by painting it a rich brown color with pale yellow-green shutters to match.
